es, specific photos, etc.). Online Media includes access to YouTube, SHOUTcast internet radio stations, Flickr and more.","Hard drive capacities come in 1TB and 2TB of available storage, which will allow users to pack the Iomega ScreenPlay Director HD with plenty of songs, photos and videos without worrying about overload.","Setting the device up is quite easy, too. Connect to an HDTV via an HDMI cable (which thankfully is included), or component and composite (RCA) cables for older televisions. USB 2.0 ports allow external hard drives to plug in easily, or the Iomega WIFI Adapter can be used to avoid having to plug in an Ethernet cable."]},"id":"a4711ef6-e6cc-4725-87ef-84209324ab08","type":"text"},{"data":{"text":"Play Personal Media"},"id":"bea849ed-b349-4ff7-a23a-05fe36022195","type":"heading"},{"data":{"paragraphs":["The ScreenPlay Director HD supports up to 1080p high definition video running at 24 frames per second (fps), which is the frame rate of Hollywood movies. High definition resolution is an important feature for home media servers, whether it&#39;s 1080p/i or 720. Video quality is great, as is sound. Stereo surround sound is supported, and sounds fantastic playing out of either a television or a good home theater sound system, which is ideal. Movies and TV shows look and sound terrific."]},"id":"6ab53db1-4dd5-4fd9-9082-a99f6d830c2b","type":"text"},{"data":{"text":"Video &amp; Sound Quality"},"id":"0410c5e2-f5cd-409e-83e3-2b5193e15ede","type":"heading"},{"data":{"paragraphs":["Users can buy or rent movies through Best Buy’s CinemaNow movie and TV show online download service, which has a wide variety of films to browse from major studio releases to independent releases. Television shows are also available for purchase. iTunes Store content (Music, movies and TV shows) isn’t supported.","Keep in mind that if you’re planning on syncing up CinemaNow purchases with your computer, those movies and TV shows are only compatible with Windows PCs (XP or Vista) with Windows Media 10 or 11. Sorry Mac users, no luck here for CinemaNow; keep in mind the ScreenPlay Director HD device is compatible with Mac OS X.","One other cool note to using CinemaNow: on a Windows PC, you can browse some titles on CinemaNow that support being burned to DVD for additional playing options and a physical back-up."]},"id":"af492276-fbcf-4d79-8b8d-10d64a25c538","type":"text"},{"data":{"text":"Purchase &amp; Rent Content"},"id":"cd25e9df-c04f-4d3e-bcc4-de39dbd21e8d","type":"heading"},{"data":{"paragraphs":["Home media servers should be able to playback a variety of personal content, which is usually in different formats. The ScreenPlay Director HD is DivX-certified, which means media encoded with the popular video codec will playback without any problems, including DivX VOD and HD. The device also supports other popular formats such as H.264, WMV, AVCHD, MPEG-1, MPEG-2, MPEG-4 and more.","The device supports a multitude of audio formats, so listening to music isn’t a problem and quite enjoyable through one’s television or a solid home theater sound setup. Some of the codecs include MP3, MP4, AC3 (Dolby Digital), WAV, OGG, non-DRM AAC and others. Unfortunately, it won’t support Apple iTunes Store purchases using Apple’s AAC, but users can easily convert those to MP3s or any other compatible codec within iTunes or with third-party software, and transfer to the ScreenPlay Director HD to enjoy."]},"id":"8f46f31f-b15e-4f05-b9ef-01f7e536a749","type":"text"},{"data":{"text":"Help &amp; Support"},"id":"07825458-0500-40ba-947b-fb35689ab928","type":"heading"},{"data":{"paragraphs":["The ScreenPlay Director HD is supported on Mac OS X systems (Intel and PowerPC) and Windows PC computers (Windows 7, XP and Vista). A USB cable connects the device to your computer to transfer media, etc. CinemaNow is Windows-only, so a Mac won&#39;t be able to rent or playback those rentals or purchases.","Tech support includes phone, 1-on-1 live chat, forums and an FAQ/Knowledge base. Plus, there’s a user’s manual and quick install guide to get up and running fast. If you have a problem, Iomega is going to make sure the issue is resolved. Both the quick install guide and user’s manual come with troubleshooting tips, which should fix most common problems."]},"id":"c8efc94d-1c5d-425b-b3aa-25577be39f5c","type":"text"},{"data":{"text":"Summary"},"id":"a7e5735b-12f2-4d8e-bd35-c5ffcbf552a8","type":"heading"},{"data":{"paragraphs":["The <strong>Iomega ScreenPlay Director HD</strong> is a marvelous media player that can support most video and audio formats, so playing your collection of home movies and music is a cinch. Renting or buying movies and TV shows from CinemaNow is a breeze and looks and sounds great. Internet media options are robust, and photos look great whether from your collection or viewing on Flickr. Overall, it’s a great device and a good price point with enough storage for all your movies, music, photos and then some, making it standout among similar home media servers.","At TopTenREVIEWS We Do the Research So You Don&#39;t Have To.™"]},"id":"d9e29eb4-25e9-42cf-a530-6ef62d81a387","type":"text"}]],"body":null,"legacyId":"product_review_page_49779","url":"/iomega-screenplay-director-hd-review","authors":[{"email":"","slug":"top-ten-reviews-staff","url":"/author/top-ten-reviews-staff","dateCreated":"2019-04-17T20:46:58Z","name":"Top Ten Reviews Staff","dateModified":"2019-04-17T20:46:58Z","id":"EcXXb3s8QKwvex3rQshgX5","dateImported":null,"site":"toptenreviews"}],"territories":["US","GB"],"companies":[],"dateCreated":"2010-06-14T19:28:21Z","datePublished":"2010-06-14T19:28:21Z","name":"Iomega ScreenPlay Director HD","synopsis":"Editor's note: This product has been removed from viewing as part of this site because it has been discontinued. You can still read our original review below, but TopTenREVIEWS is no longer updating this product's information.","review":{"rating":95,"verdict":"The Iomega ScreenPlay Director HD is a fantastic